summary: I must thank you. Before I read your stories, I didn't believe Daenerys and Stannis could ever work as a pairing, but how wrong...
question: I must thank you. Before I read your stories, I didn't believe Daenerys and Stannis could ever work as a pairing, but how wrong I was. Two of the most just and legitimate rulers bonding over their similarities, and putting aside differences to defend Westeros against a common foe? How could that not work, especially in the hands of such a great writer like yourself. I feel inspired to write a story of my own, a long-fic centred around Stannerys, and that inspiration only exists thanks to you.
answer:
Dear Anonymous,

A very happy Friday to you and thank you so, so much for this incredibly kind message! I am so thrilled to hear that you read and enjoyed my Stannis/Dany fics and that you are inspired to write your own! You are exactly correct in your assessment of the characters and that’s exactly why I started shipping them as soon as I read A Clash of Kings. I am so happy to hear you think I’m a great writer! Thank you again. <3

I would absolutely love to support you and read your fic when you choose to write it, so please do keep in touch (whether on Anon or off, whatever with which you’re comfortable) and let me know if you decide to post it here and on AO3! We definitely need more lovely folks like yourself who love these characters creating content.

Again, please do come talk to me anytime. I’m sending lots of love and gratitude!

tags: just some of my fave dany quotes
summary: “So many men have tried to kill me, I don't remember all their names. I have been sold like a broodmare. I've been chained and...
body:
“So many men have tried to kill me, I don’t remember all their names. I have been sold like a broodmare. I’ve been chained and betrayed, raped and defiled. Do you know what kept me standing through all those years in exile? Faith. Not in any gods. Not in myths and legends. In myself. In Daenerys Targaryen…I was born to rule the Seven Kingdoms, and I will.”

“Woman? Is that meant to insult me? I would return the slap if I took you for a man.”

“The next time you raise a hand to me will be the last time you have hands.”
